    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-27T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="457"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.00 Revolutions/389: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at São Paulo</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CCR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cameron</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-27T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 27, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 24, 2 p.m. If, as the Department understands, the Brazilian
                    Government is maintaining an actual, effective blockade of the port of Santos,
                    this Government cannot protest as requested by the American Chamber of
                    Commerce.</p>
                <p>Inform Embassy.</p>
                <p>The Department feels that it cannot properly forward the resolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
